cockateil i just got a cockateil yesterday from my dad's friend he is a yello male who is the conditions he was living in were exceptional but not great he seems very healthy eating preening chirping lively and there are no visable sings of any sicknress i saw a little blood on his beak so i checked him out he has a partially scabbed soar about the size of a dime on his back it doesn't seem to be pestering him too much but when i touchrf around it he did not appreciate it what could have caused it what do i do why does he keep picking it no he isn't pulling out his feathers because there are no feathers at the bottom also we can't afford to go to the vet so don 't tell me that well you could try putting some antibiotic ointment on the scab if you think it is infected i would have no idea what might have caused the injury he might have fallen in the cage and scraped his back he picks at the scab for the same reason that people will pick at a scab it is new and unusual and may feel uncomfortable or even hurt sometimes you can put a cloth collar on a bird's neck chest or back to prevent picking at a wound if you would like detailed instructions for this e mail me and i will direct you to the yahoo group that has files on this procedure i understand about financial problems that being said i would recommend that you try to put aside a small amount of money each pay day for a vet fund in case your bird does need help the bird depends upon you for his health please do not let him down good luck Equine conformation Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Pneumonia First aid Smallpox Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Tattoo Domestic rabbit Guinea pig Prostate cancer Breastfeeding Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Fecal incontinence Piccolo Junior Saga Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hearing impairment Traumatic brain injury Bird Stomach cancer Eczema Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Fancy rat Urinary incontinence Psoriasis HIV test Hypoglycemia Hamster Weight training Condom Microecono